      Three spatial concepts are woven into the fabric of all Spirit system components, creating a unified visual order: <b>inset</b> space within components, vertical <b>stack</b> space between elements and components, and horizontal <b>inline</b> spacing between elements in a row. 
  {% endfilter %}
  {% filter markdown %}
      ## Inset
      An inset applies padding on all sides of a block or inline element. By default, all four sides are equal. 
      <img src="/images/inset@2x.png" alt="Inset at X (8px), 2X (16px), or 3X (24px)" />
      Apply an inset token to any container, such as a card or a or table cell, to create consistent padding around the content.
 
