      ## Inline

      Inline spacing separates inline elements by consistent applying space on one side of each element. By default, left-aligned elements have right-side spacing (as shown). Right-aligned elements are the opposite. 

      <img src="/images/inline@2x.png" alt="Inline at X (8px), 2X (16px), or 3X (24px)" />
 
      Use inline spacing to separate text, such as the inline links in a footer, or block elements, such as pills, tabs, or buttons. 

      <img src="/images/inline-example@2x.png" alt="Inline example: a row of tabs showing the inline space between each tab" />
  
      #### Tokens

      Left-aligned items use inline-left, which adds spacing to their right. This ensures the first item is flush left.
  {% endfilter %}
    <table>(table)</table>
  {% filter markdown %}
      Right-aligned items use inline-right, which adds spacing to their left. This ensures the last item is flush right. 
